'''Fellowship Plaza''' was a public space built by the [[Reconstruction Authority]], located in the [[Senate District/Legends|Senate District]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], in between the [[New Jedi Temple|Jedi Temple]] and the [[Galactic Justice Center]].

==History==
Built in the wake of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]]'s [[Yuuzhan Vong War|invasion]] of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], Fellowship Plaza was a large public space dedicated to beauty and contemplation. Strategically located between the Jedi Temple and the Justice Center, it served to unify the two complexes as a common entrance way.

In [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], [[Lumiya]] and [[Alema Rar]] [[Duel in the Fellowship Plaza|killed]] [[Tresina Lobi]] there after a meeting Lumiya had with [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]].

[[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] and [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] escaped into the Plaza after an attempt to arrest them by a squad of [[Galactic Alliance Guard]] soldiers during the [[Funeral of Mara Jade Skywalker]]. In [[43 ABY]], Jedi Knights [[Bazel Warv]] and [[Yaqeel Saav'etu]] traveled through the Plaza to return to the Temple. However before they entered their home, they contracted [[Force psychosis]] and had to be detained by [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] and her husband, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]].

==Layout==
Fellowship Plaza occupied the rooftop of the city block in front of the [[Temple district/Legends|Temple Precinct]]. Famed for its [[Walking Garden]], which contained neatly trimmed [[blartree]]s, it was usually abandoned after dark. The Jedi Temple could be seen from the Plaza, with the [[Processional Way/Legends|Processional Way]] beginning where the Walking Garden ended.

